The paper deals with Visual Question Answering (VQA), which involves both computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel co-attention mechanism for VQA, which involves modeling the question and image attention hierarchically, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also uses convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which are commonly used in machine learning and deep learning, suggesting that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
